---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Running Coach"
  description="Running Coach turns training data into a clear weekly running plan."
  pathname="/"
>
  <article class="shell landing-page">
    <header class="landing-hero">
      <div class="landing-hero__intro">
        <p class="eyebrow">Running Coach</p>
        <h1>Turn your training data into a clear weekly running plan.</h1>
        <p class="lede landing-hero__lede">
          Connect your training data, review recent context, and get a week that is
          easier to understand and follow.
        </p>
        <div class="landing-actions">
          <a class="button button--primary" href="/login">Open portal</a>
          <a class="button button--secondary" href="/privacy">Read privacy</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <section class="landing-preview" aria-labelledby="landing-preview-title">
        <p id="landing-preview-title" class="eyebrow">This week</p>
        <div class="landing-preview__hero" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="landing-preview__split" aria-hidden="true">
          <div></div>
          <div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="landing-preview__footer" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      </section>
    </header>

    <section class="landing-value-row" aria-label="Product summary">
      <article class="landing-value-card">
        <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
        <h2>Turns recent training context into a simpler weekly plan.</h2>
        <p>
          The goal is not a dashboard full of metrics. The goal is a week you can
          actually review and act on.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="landing-value-card landing-value-card--tint">
        <p class="eyebrow">Who it is for</p>
        <h2>For runners who already track training and want clearer guidance.</h2>
        <p>
          Useful when the data already exists but the next week still feels too hard to
          piece together by hand.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="how-it-works" class="landing-flow" aria-labelledby="landing-flow-title">
      <h2 id="landing-flow-title">How it works</h2>
      <div class="landing-flow__grid">
        <article class="landing-step">
          <p class="eyebrow">01</p>
          <h3>Connect your training data</h3>
          <p>
            Authorize Running Coach to read the training data it needs from connected
            services.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="landing-step">
          <p class="eyebrow">02</p>
          <h3>Review recent context</h3>
          <p>
            Use recent activity and training context to understand what the runner has
            actually been doing.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="landing-step">
          <p class="eyebrow">03</p>
          <h3>Get a clearer week</h3>
          <p>
            Turn that context into guidance that is easier to review, trust, and follow
            week by week.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="landing-trust" aria-label="Trust and status">
      <article class="landing-trust__primary">
        <p class="eyebrow">Privacy and trust</p>
        <h2>Clear about connected data use.</h2>
        <p>
          The privacy page explains what data is used, why it is used, and how to
          request disconnection or deletion.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="landing-trust__meta">
        <p class="eyebrow">Current status</p>
        <p>Early stage, focused on clarity and credibility.</p>
        <p>Portal access sits behind a simple public site.</p>
      </aside>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
